      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:6:8:35:2",
      "relations": null,
      "text": [
        " مَا زَادَ مِنَ اللِّحْيَةِ عَنِ الْقَبْضَةِ فَهُوَ فِي النَّارِ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Al Husayn Bin Muhammad, from Moala Bin Muhammad, and Ali Bin Muhammad, from Salih Bin Abu Hammad, altogether from Al Washa, from Ahmad Bin A’aiz, from Abu Khadeeja, from Moala Bin Khunays, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘Whatever exceeds from the beard from the fist, so it is in the Fire’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "2. Al-Husayn ibn Muhammad has narrated from Mu‘alla’ ibn Muhammad and Ali ibn Muhammad from Salih ibn abu Hammad all from al-Washsha’ from Ahmad ibn ‘ A’idh from abu Khadijah from Mu’alla’ ibn Khunayth who has said the following: “Abu ‘Abd Allah, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, has said, ’Whatever of the beard exceeds one’s fistful is in the fire.’” "
        ]
      }
    }
